text.__SUMMARY__: Habenaria maitlandii is a species of plant in the family Orchidaceae. It is endemic to Cameroon.  Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical dry lowland grassland. It is threatened by habitat loss.
text.Sources: Cheek, M. & Pollard, B.J. (2000). "Habenaria maitlandii". The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. IUCN. 2000: e.T39937A10293308. doi:10.2305/IUCN.UK.2000.RLTS.T39937A10293308.en. Retrieved 19 December 2017.
